<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="Pet_Care_Assistant.Views.AboutUsPage"
             Title="About Us"
             BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryBackgroundColor}">

    <!-- 
    Note: FontSize and TextColor are not manually set for most elements.
    They automatically inherit global styles from 'Styles.xaml'
    and will respond to theme changes and font scaling preferences.
    -->

    <ContentPage.Resources>
        <!-- Local style for section titles on this page -->
        <Style x:Key="SectionTitleStyle" TargetType="Label">
            <Setter Property="FontAttributes" Value="Bold" />
            <!-- Added an Accent color option – can be defined in Colors.xaml -->
            <!-- <Setter Property="TextColor" Value="{DynamicResource AccentColor}" /> -->
            <Setter Property="Margin" Value="0, 0, 0, 10" />
            <!-- FontSize will be automatically inherited from global styles -->
        </Style>
    </ContentPage.Resources>

    <ScrollView>
        <VerticalStackLayout Spacing="20" Padding="25">

            <!-- Section: About Us -->
            <Frame>
                <VerticalStackLayout Spacing="10">
                    <Label Text="Our Mission" Style="{StaticResource SectionTitleStyle}" />
                    <Label>
                        We are a clinic dedicated to excellence in veterinary medicine. Our mission is to provide the highest standard of medical care across all our centers, restoring health and offering a new chance at life to your beloved companions. Here, every patient is treated with empathy and professionalism — like a true member of the family.
                    </Label>
                </VerticalStackLayout>
            </Frame>

            <!-- Section: Contact -->
            <Frame>
                <VerticalStackLayout Spacing="10">
                    <Label Text="Contact Details" Style="{StaticResource SectionTitleStyle}" />

                    <!-- Grid for neat alignment -->
                    <Grid RowSpacing="10" ColumnSpacing="10"
                          RowDefinitions="Auto, Auto, Auto"
                          ColumnDefinitions="Auto, *">

                        <!-- Phone -->
                        <Label Grid.Row="0" Grid.Column="0" Text="Phone:" FontAttributes="Bold" />
                        <Label Grid.Row="0" Grid.Column="1" Text="0785 296 378" />

                        <!-- Email -->
                        <Label Grid.Row="1" Grid.Column="0" Text="Email:" FontAttributes="Bold" />
                        <Label Grid.Row="1" Grid.Column="1" Text="petcareassistant@gmail.com" />

                        <!-- Address -->
                        <Label Grid.Row="2" Grid.Column="0" Text="Address:" FontAttributes="Bold" />
                        <Label Grid.Row="2" Grid.Column="1" Text="1 Hope Street, District 1, Bucharest" />
                    </Grid>
                </VerticalStackLayout>
            </Frame>

            <!-- Section: Schedule -->
            <Frame>
                <VerticalStackLayout Spacing="10">
                    <Label Text="Working Hours" Style="{StaticResource SectionTitleStyle}" />
                    <Label Text="Monday – Sunday: Open 24/7" FontAttributes="Bold" />
                    <Label Text="Our clinic is open non-stop, ready to handle any emergency at any hour." />
                </VerticalStackLayout>
            </Frame>

            <!-- Section: Terms and Conditions (Expandable) -->
            <Frame>
                <VerticalStackLayout Spacing="10">
                    <!-- The clickable header (with arrow) -->
                    <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing="10" VerticalOptions="Center">
                        <Label Text="Terms and Conditions" Style="{StaticResource SectionTitleStyle}" Margin="0"/>
                        <Label x:Name="ArrowLabel" Text="›" FontSize="Large" FontAttributes="Bold" VerticalOptions="Center"/>

                        <!-- Gesture Recognizer triggers logic in the code-behind -->
                        <HorizontalStackLayout.GestureRecognizers>
                            <TapGestureRecognizer Tapped="OnTermsTapped" />
                        </HorizontalStackLayout.GestureRecognizers>
                    </HorizontalStackLayout>

                    <Label Text="Tap here to read the application's Terms and Conditions of Use." />

                    <!-- Hidden content, controlled from code-behind -->
                    <Label x:Name="TermsContentLabel"
                           IsVisible="False"
                           Text="Acceptance of Terms of Use 
Welcome to 'Pet Care Assistant'. By downloading, installing, or using this mobile application, you ('the User') confirm that you have read, understood, and fully agree to abide by the terms and conditions outlined in this document. If you do not agree with these terms, please refrain from using the application.

Purpose and Use of the Application 
This application is designed as a digital tool to assist clients of our veterinary clinic in managing information and monitoring the health of their pets. Its functionalities include, but are not limited to, appointment management, medical history storage, and receiving relevant notifications. The application is intended strictly for personal, non-commercial use. Any use beyond this designated purpose, including illegal activities, is strictly prohibited.

Data Privacy 
Your privacy is our top priority. All data entered, including personal information and your pets’ medical records, are stored locally on your device and handled with the highest level of security. Our clinic is committed to not sharing, selling, or distributing this data to third parties without your explicit consent, except when required by law.

Limitation of Liability and Medical Disclaimer 
'Pet Care Assistant' is a management and informational tool — not a substitute for professional veterinary diagnosis. The information, reminders, or medical data presented in the application are for guidance purposes only and should never replace an in-person consultation with a licensed veterinarian. The clinic assumes no responsibility for medical decisions based solely on data from the app or for any potential data loss caused by misuse or device malfunction." />

                </VerticalStackLayout>
            </Frame>

        </VerticalStackLayout>
    </ScrollView>
</ContentPage>
